2.30	Sushurata	Sushruta	Suśruta (Sanskrit: सुश्रुत (sʊʃɾʊt̪), fl. 800 BCE) was an ancient Indian surgeon and is the author of the book Suśruta Saṃhitā, in which he describes over 300 surgical procedures, 120 surgical instruments and classifies human surgery in eight categories. He lived, taught and practiced his art on the banks of the Ganges in the area that corresponds to the present day city of Varanasi in North India.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/74/Shushrut_statue.jpg/320px-Shushrut_statue.jpg
